aiResponses.unnamed_7:
Experienced IT management and analytics professional with an MS in Information Technology Management from University of Texas at Dallas and a B.Tech in Electronics & Communication from Lovely Professional University. I bring a strong blend of technical skills (Python, SQL, R, HTML, React JS), data visualization (Tableau, Power BI, Google Analytics), and product delivery experience using Agile frameworks (Scrum, Kanban) and tools (Jira, Trello).

At SYNYCS TECHNOLOGIES and theworkgallery.com I collaborated across engineering, product, and design teams to deliver analytics solutions and product features. I focus on translating business requirements into measurable dashboards and reliable data pipelines, and I enjoy mentoring teams on Lean Startup principles to iterate quickly and deliver customer value.
aiResponses.resume: https://vinay.portfolio (full resume and project details available on portfolio; LinkedIn: https://linkedin.com/in/ivinaymr)
aiResponses.cover_letter:
I am excited to apply and bring 6+ years of experience in product-focused analytics and IT management to your team. My graduate education at the University of Texas at Dallas sharpened my ability to align technical work with strategic goals, and my roles at SYNYCS TECHNOLOGIES and theworkgallery.com gave me hands-on experience building data products, dashboards, and customer-facing features. I have led cross-functional efforts using Scrum and Kanban, ensuring clear priorities and rapid, quality deliveries.

In my previous roles I built and maintained analytics dashboards and reporting pipelines using Tableau and Power BI, and implemented SQL- and Python-based ETL processes to ensure reliable data for decision making. I partnered directly with product managers and stakeholders to define success metrics and created dashboards that enabled stakeholders to act on insights quickly. I enjoy balancing hands-on technical contributions with mentoring colleagues on agile practices and data literacy.

I am particularly excited about roles that combine analytics, product thinking, and cross-team collaboration. My portfolio (https://vinay.portfolio) highlights examples of dashboard work and product initiatives. I look forward to the opportunity to discuss how my skills in data visualization, analytics engineering, and Agile delivery can support your team and drive measurable outcomes.
